Directions, Parking, and Places to Stay | UIC Admissions                  Explore UIC  Visit Virtually  Apply    S      Search Input     Submit        M       Directions, Parking, and Places to Stay        Home  Book a Visit  You are here     Home  Book a Visit  You are here              Did you know?     DEPTH         i                     Due to the COVID-19 pandemic UIC continues to accept undergraduate first-year and transfer applications for the Fall 2020 semester.            Getting around UIC    Directions to UIC  UIC Admissions holds events at various locations around campus. Please refer to your registration confirmation for the most accurate arrival and location information.  Mass Transit, Driving, etc.  Circle Interchange Project  Information on renovation project including the temporary closing of the Harrison St. Bridge between Halsted and Des Plaines and detours of CTA Buses.   Parking  Parking at UIC  Parking and Directions to Specific Buildings  Office of Admissions, Student Services Building (SSB)  UIC Visitors Center, Student Services Building (SSB)  Student Center East (SCE)  Student Center West (SCW)  James Stukel Towers (JST)  UIC Pavilion  Bike Stations  A DIVVY bike station is located at SSB at Racine and Harrison in addition to several other DIVVY bike stations across campus.  Also, a bike rack for locking bicycles is located at the main entrance of SSB.         Places to Stay     Special Rates for Nearby Hotels  Chicago Marriott at Medical District/UIC 625 S. Ashland Avenue Located two blocks west of the UIC Campus. UIC has a special rate For individual reservations call (800) 356-3641 and ask for the UIC Special Rate, for Group Reservations contact the Sales Manager (312) 529-6002 or email DOS@marriottchicagomd.com Make a reservation  La Quinta Inn Chicago Downtown 1 South Franklin Street Nestled 1.5 miles East of the UIC Campus; the La Quinta Inn Chicago offers a special UIC rate with a deluxe continental breakfast and complimentary internet. For group reservations and questions please call Tim Bailey at (312) 558-1020 ext. 5502 or email at Tim.Bailey@laquinta.com Make a reservation  Crowne Plaza Chicago West Loop  733 W Madison St Located seven blocks north of the UIC Campus. Offering discounted rates for UIC. Call in to book the "UIC" rate at (312) 829-5000 or make your reservation online. For inquires please contact, Sam Matassa at (312) 602-2175. Make a reservation  Club Quarters, Central Loop 111 West Adams Street Located 1.7 miles east of the UIC campus. Club Quarters offers low member rates in 15 prime downtown locations in the US and London to all University of Illinois travelers. For reservations, call (203) 905-2100 and mention member organization "University of Illinois" or reserve online (password: UOI).  Club Quarters, Wacker at Michigan 75 East Wacker Drive Located 2.8 miles northeast of the UIC campus. Club Quarters offers low member rates in 15 prime downtown locations in the US and London to all University of Illinois travelers. For reservations, call (203) 905-2100 and mention member organization "University of Illinois" or reserve online (password: UOI).                             Related Resources    Directions to Specific Buildings  Visit Campus  Explore UIC  Contact Admissions                    UnderGraduate      Graduate & Professional                 Office of Admissions  Main Office  1200 West Harrison Street Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Phone: (312) 996-4350 Contact UIC Admissions    Visitors Center  1220 West Harrison Street Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Phone: (312) 413-1726                 Mailing Address  Undergraduate  Office of Undergraduate Admissions (MC 018) University of Illinois at Chicago 1200 West Harrison Street, Suite 1100 Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Contact Undergraduate Admissions     Graduate & Professional  The graduate and professional application process is paperless. Please do not mail materials unless expressly requested. Contact Graduate and Professional Admissions  